This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it proposes a method for generating adversarial images that are imperceptible to the human eye. It also mentions the potential for further improvement if image semantics are taken into account, which is a common topic in computer vision research.

The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it discusses the use of adversarial images to protect the content of images shared online from unethical machine learning classifiers. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the paper proposes a method for generating adversarial images using a differentiable color filter, which is a technique commonly used in deep learning.

Cybersecurity and cryptography (cs.CR) is also a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of adversarial images to protect the content of images shared online from unethical machine learning classifiers, which can be seen as a security issue.

Finally, multimedia (cs.MM) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the photographic quality and appeal of adversarial images, which are important factors in multimedia applications.
